    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_53979344" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/53979344" />
    <a title="Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2244048-kelly"><img alt="Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1290525847p2/2244048.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/53979344?book_show_action=true">Apr 25, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly" href="/user/show/2244048-kelly">Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780192840851" href="/book/show/207743.The_Oxford_Book_of_English_Ghost_Stories">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer53979344" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13252500393473635671">Ok, confession: I read a majority of this book in the stacks while working at the library. Don&apos;t judge me--if you had to shelf-read for hours on end, you would take the occasional break to. But anyway, I loved the stories in this book. They&apos;re the old-fashioned, downright creepy stories that are, unfortunately, seldom seen nowadays. My favorites were The Monkey&apos;s Paw and this story about a creepy bird-like creature that I can&apos;t remember the title of (it was the simplest story yet I can&apos;t help bu</span>
  <span id="freeText13252500393473635671" style="display:none">Ok, confession: I read a majority of this book in the stacks while working at the library. Don't judge me--if you had to shelf-read for hours on end, you would take the occasional break to. But anyway, I loved the stories in this book. They're the old-fashioned, downright creepy stories that are, unfortunately, seldom seen nowadays. My favorites were The Monkey's Paw and this story about a creepy bird-like creature that I can't remember the title of (it was the simplest story yet I can't help but think about it whenever I'm in a empty house). If you're ever in the mood for something scary, check this book out. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13252500393473635671" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

